7. IMPLEMENT THE CONCEPT OF POINTERS, CALL BY VALUE AND CALL BY FUNCTION
====================================================================
Objective:
Understand mutation semantics in room/state updates.

Colab Project Mapping:
- Pointer receivers are used where shared room state must be mutated safely and intentionally.
- Value copies are preferred for transform-style helpers to avoid accidental side effects.
- This distinction is critical in collaborative scenarios where subtle state mutation bugs can desync clients.

Go Example:
```go
func AddPointByValue(points []Point, p Point) []Point {
    // slice header is copied by value, underlying array may still be shared
    return append(points, p)
}

func IncrementThicknessByPointer(e *DrawEvent) {
    e.Thickness++
}

func ReplaceColorValue(e DrawEvent, color string) DrawEvent {
    e.Color = color
    return e
}
```

Mermaid: Value vs Pointer Effect
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[DrawEvent value copy] --> B[ReplaceColorValue]
    B --> C[Returns new value]

    D[DrawEvent pointer] --> E[IncrementThicknessByPointer]
    E --> F[Original object mutated]
```

