9. IMPLEMENT THE CONCEPT OF CONCURRENCY
====================================================================
Objective:
Use goroutines, channels, and mutex for room broadcast and state safety.

Colab Project Mapping:
- Each whiteboard room behaves as a concurrent stream with multiple readers and writers.
- Buffered channels and non-blocking publish logic keep one slow client from degrading room-wide latency.
- Mutex-protected subscriber registry ensures safe concurrent join/leave and event fanout.

Go Example:
```go
import "sync"

type Hub struct {
    mu          sync.RWMutex
    subscribers map[string][]chan DrawEvent
}

func NewHub() *Hub {
    return &Hub{subscribers: map[string][]chan DrawEvent{}}
}

func (h *Hub) Subscribe(roomID string) <-chan DrawEvent {
    ch := make(chan DrawEvent, 32)
    h.mu.Lock()
    h.subscribers[roomID] = append(h.subscribers[roomID], ch)
    h.mu.Unlock()
    return ch
}

func (h *Hub) Publish(roomID string, e DrawEvent) {
    h.mu.RLock()
    targets := append([]chan DrawEvent{}, h.subscribers[roomID]...)
    h.mu.RUnlock()

    for _, ch := range targets {
        select {
        case ch <- e:
        default:
            // drop on slow consumer to avoid blocking producer
        }
    }
}
```

Mermaid: Concurrent Event Fanout
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Producer goroutine] --> B[Hub.Publish]
    B --> C1[Subscriber ch1]
    B --> C2[Subscriber ch2]
    B --> C3[Subscriber ch3]
    C1 --> D1[Client 1]
    C2 --> D2[Client 2]
    C3 --> D3[Client 3]
```

