10. IMPLEMENT THE CONCEPT OF VARIABLES, VALUES AND TYPE
====================================================================
Objective:
Consolidate production-readiness practices used in the Collab whiteboard implementation.

Submission-Oriented Summary:
- Backend quality: typed models, explicit error handling, interface-based service boundaries, and concurrency-safe fanout.
- Frontend integration quality: contract-consistent JSON payloads, predictable response semantics, and real-time event synchronization behavior.
- Maintainability: concept-wise implementation enables easier onboarding, debugging, and incremental enhancement.
- Extensibility: architecture supports adding board persistence, role-based event filtering, and horizontal event distribution.

Checklist:
- Use domain types (`ToolType`, `RoomID`, `UserID`) instead of raw strings where possible.
- Use zero-value safe structs.
- Keep exported fields JSON-tagged for API compatibility.
- Prefer explicit types in service boundaries and inferred types inside function bodies.
- Keep frontend and backend event names/versioning aligned to avoid protocol drift.
- Add integration tests for join/leave/broadcast edge cases before production rollout.

Mermaid: Type Safety Emphasis
```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Raw Input JSON] --> B[Typed Struct Decode]
    B --> C[Validation]
    C --> D[Business Function]
    D --> E[Typed Output + JSON Encode]
```

